h3. Issue Summary

In DVCS accounts page, "Search for repositories" doesn't work when using MySQL database

h3. Steps to Reproduce

- Jira Software Server: v8.16.0, v8.16.1
- DB: MySQL

# Configure DVCS account(GitHub, Bitbucket, etc.)
# Input search query in "Search for repositories" form.
# Search result is wrong, "We couldn't show any results. Try searching again, or check your Jira log file." will be shown.
#* If you search with "NAME", all repositories will be displayed.

h3. Expected Results

Search result is correct, same as PostgreSQL one.

h3. Actual Results

Search result is wrong, "We couldn't show any results. Try searching again, or check your Jira log file." will be shown.
In the following environment, searching with query "aaa" should be work as expected as PostgreSQL one.

*Evidence*

- MySQL
-- query=NAME, hit
--- result  !jira_mysql-dvcs-NAME-hit.png|thumbnail! 
--- SQL log
{code}
2021-09-21 09:23:25,119+0000 http-nio-8080-exec-1 admin 563x294x1 pkkvd1 /rest/bitbucket/1.0/repository/findByName 2 ms "SELECT FORK_OF_SLUG,FORK_OF_OWNER,SMARTCOMMITS_ENABLED,DELETED,LOGO,SLUG,ACTIVITY_LAST_SYNC,NAME,FORK_OF_NAME,LINKED,LAST_CHANGESET_NODE,REMOTE_ID,REPOSITORY_URL,UPDATE_LINK_AUTHORISED,ID,ORGANIZATION_ID,LAST_COMMIT_DATE,FORK FROM AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING WHERE DELETED = ?  AND LINKED = ?  AND UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)  ORDER BY NAME LIMIT 100" {1=false, 2=true, 3=%NAME%}
{code}
-- query=aaa, nohit
--- result  !jira_mysql-dvcs-aaa-nohit.png|thumbnail! 
--- SQL log
{code}
2021-09-21 09:23:38,322+0000 http-nio-8080-exec-7 admin 563x295x1 pkkvd1 /rest/bitbucket/1.0/repository/findByName 3 ms "SELECT FORK_OF_SLUG,FORK_OF_OWNER,SMARTCOMMITS_ENABLED,DELETED,LOGO,SLUG,ACTIVITY_LAST_SYNC,NAME,FORK_OF_NAME,LINKED,LAST_CHANGESET_NODE,REMOTE_ID,REPOSITORY_URL,UPDATE_LINK_AUTHORISED,ID,ORGANIZATION_ID,LAST_COMMIT_DATE,FORK FROM AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING WHERE DELETED = ?  AND LINKED = ?  AND UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)  ORDER BY NAME LIMIT 100" {1=false, 2=true, 3=%aaa%}
{code}
- PostgreSQL(Expected)
-- query=NAME, nohit
--- result  !jira_postgresql-dvcs-NAME-nohit.png|thumbnail! 
--- SQL log
{code}
2021-09-21 09:21:03,210+0000 http-nio-8080-exec-2 admin 561x322x1 fvokc1 /rest/bitbucket/1.0/repository/findByName 1 ms "SELECT "FORK_OF_SLUG","FORK_OF_OWNER","SMARTCOMMITS_ENABLED","DELETED","LOGO","SLUG","ACTIVITY_LAST_SYNC","NAME","FORK_OF_NAME","LINKED","LAST_CHANGESET_NODE","REMOTE_ID","REPOSITORY_URL","UPDATE_LINK_AUTHORISED","ID","ORGANIZATION_ID","LAST_COMMIT_DATE","FORK" FROM public."AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING" WHERE "DELETED" = ?  AND "LINKED" = ?  AND UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)  ORDER BY "NAME" LIMIT 100" {1=false, 2=true, 3=%NAME%}
{code}
-- query=aaa, hit
--- result  !jira_postgresql-dvcs-aaa-hit.png|thumbnail! 
--- SQL log
{code}
2021-09-21 09:21:52,568+0000 http-nio-8080-exec-12 admin 561x323x1 fvokc1 /rest/bitbucket/1.0/repository/findByName 3 ms "SELECT "FORK_OF_SLUG","FORK_OF_OWNER","SMARTCOMMITS_ENABLED","DELETED","LOGO","SLUG","ACTIVITY_LAST_SYNC","NAME","FORK_OF_NAME","LINKED","LAST_CHANGESET_NODE","REMOTE_ID","REPOSITORY_URL","UPDATE_LINK_AUTHORISED","ID","ORGANIZATION_ID","LAST_COMMIT_DATE","FORK" FROM public."AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING" WHERE "DELETED" = ?  AND "LINKED" = ?  AND UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)  ORDER BY "NAME" LIMIT 100" {1=false, 2=true, 3=%aaa%}
{code}

h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available


h4. Note

Using PostgreSQL DB doesn't affected.

It seems WHERE clause `UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)` in MySQL doesn't work as intent.
{code}
"SELECT FORK_OF_SLUG,FORK_OF_OWNER,SMARTCOMMITS_ENABLED,DELETED,LOGO,SLUG,ACTIVITY_LAST_SYNC,NAME,FORK_OF_NAME,LINKED,LAST_CHANGESET_NODE,REMOTE_ID,REPOSITORY_URL,UPDATE_LINK_AUTHORISED,ID,ORGANIZATION_ID,LAST_COMMIT_DATE,FORK FROM AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING WHERE DELETED = ?  AND LINKED = ?  AND UPPER("NAME") LIKE UPPER(?)  ORDER BY NAME LIMIT 100" {1=false, 2=true, 3=%NAME%}
{code}
